data.description: Under contract-accepting backup offers. This spacious 2 bedroom, 1 bathroom Pinellas Park home features multiple major updates for buyer’s peace of mind (New roof and soffit in 2016, hurricane impact windows and doors throughout in 2016, water softener system in 2016, and a new 2.5 split HVAC in 2020!) as well as making it a perfect backdrop for all your design inspirations. Situated on a shady over-sized lot with well-maintained mature oaks, and a striking brick paved driveway that leads to the convenient and welcoming awning covered front door. Step inside and be greeted by the bright open concept living room, complete with built-in shelving and newer wood grained laminate flooring that can be found throughout the home. The centrally located kitchen flows seamlessly to all the main living space areas and features white shaker cabinets with modern fixtures, recessed lighting, and contrasting all-black appliances. Adjacent to the kitchen you will find a formal dining room, currently utilized as an office space, with built-in shelving and wide triple-pane windows offering plenty of natural light, in addition to access to the inside utility area as well as the garage. Sitting next to the dining room and off the kitchen is a massive family room that overlooks the huge backyard (perfectly sized for a pool with room to spare!) that can be easily accessed via the double sliding doors. Centrally located and minutes away from US 19 and I-275, making commutes to downtown St. Petersburg, Clearwater, the Gulf beaches, and even Tampa a breeze, and allowing you to conveniently enjoy all the shopping, entertainment, and dining of the area. Additionally, the home has recently appraised at value, so don't miss your chance to see this beauty, come take a look today!
